<h2><u>AFTER SUBMISSION</u></h2>
<p>If you have submitted a Visa Application at Sri Lanka visa application center in colombo, you can check your application status by providing Passport Number and Date of Birth.
</p>

<b><U>Collection of Documentation/Notification Letter Applicable</U></b>
<p>If your Visa Application are approved we will send you an email.</p>


<button class="collapsible"><font s></font>What happens if a visa Application is Refused?</button>
<div class="content">
  <p>Reconsideration of a refused application for a Visa is not possible.</p>
</div>


<button class="collapsible">Why was the application for a visa refused?</button>
<div class="content">
  <p>Visa applications are refused where a decision maker is not satisfied an applicant meets all legal requirements for the grant of a visa. If there is information addressing those refusal reasons or a change in circumstance since the previous application, you can lodge a new application along with the new or additional information.</p>
</div>


<button class="collapsible">How will the passport be returned?</button>
<div class="content">
  <p>The passport will be returned via courier to the address provided by you at the time of application or will be made available for collection from the Sri Lanka Visa Application Centre if requested.</p>
</div>
